Project Report 
 Overview

This project is a Streamlit-based Movie Recommendation System designed to suggest films using multiple machine learning techniques. The system goes beyond basic keyword matching and incorporates both statistical 
text analysis (TF-IDF) and deep semantic understanding (Sentence Transformers) to improve recommendation quality.

The goal is to build a system that not only recommends similar movies, but also understands meaning, context, and user intent behind movie descriptions.

#Objective

The main objective of this project is:

To design a hybrid recommendation system that improves movie suggestions using both lexical similarity and semantic understanding of movie content.

It also aims to make recommendations more interactive by integrating ratings, popularity, and YouTube trailers.

#Dataset

The dataset includes movie metadata such as:

Title
Overview
Genres
Tagline
Vote average
Popularity

The dataset is automatically fetched from Google Drive and preprocessed for machine learning tasks.

⚙️ Methodology
1. Data Preprocessing
Removed duplicates and missing values
Extracted and cleaned genres
Combined overview, tagline, and genres into a unified text field
Applied NLP preprocessing (tokenization, stopword removal, lemmatization)

2. Feature Engineering

A combined text feature called tags was created:

tags = overview + genres + tagline

This allows the model to understand movies as complete semantic objects instead of isolated attributes.

3. Recommendation Models

#TF-IDF Based Model
Converts text into numerical vectors
Uses cosine similarity
Focuses on word overlap
Works well for surface-level similarity

# Semantic Model (Sentence Transformers)
Uses pre-trained transformer model (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
Converts movie descriptions into embeddings
 Captures deep contextual meaning

# Hybrid Model

Combines both:

Final Score = 0.5 × TF-IDF + 0.5 × Semantic Similarity

Balances keyword matching + contextual understanding

#Genre-Based Filtering
Simple rule-based filtering using extracted genres
Allows user-driven exploration

#Extra Feature: Trailer Integration

The system dynamically fetches YouTube trailers for recommended movies, improving user experience and interpretability.

#Key Insights
TF-IDF performs well for similar wording but lacks depth
Semantic model captures meaning even when words differ
Hybrid model provides the most balanced and accurate recommendations
Movie popularity and ratings improve recommendation context
Real-world recommendation systems require multiple signals, not just text similarity

