# 11. What is the difference between my Movie Recommender System and AI Music Recommender System?

 The main difference lies in the type of data, how similarity is defined, and how user intent is interpreted.

In the Movie Recommender System, the focus is on:

Text-based similarity (overview, genres, tagline)
TF-IDF and semantic embeddings
Story and thematic similarity between movies
Recommendation is mainly based on plot and content meaning

So it answers:

“What movies are similar in story or theme?”

In the AI Music Recommender System, the focus is more complex because music is emotional and multi-dimensional:

Combines text (artist, genre, metadata) + audio features (energy, tempo, valence, danceability)
Uses hybrid scoring (NLP + audio intelligence)
Includes real-world signals like mood and vibe
Adds 30-second audio previews + album covers via API

So it answers:

“What song feels similar, not just what looks similar in metadata?”

Key Insight 

 Movie recommendation = semantic storytelling similarity
 Music recommendation = emotional + acoustic + semantic similarity

